-- Ruble Stays Little Changed Versus Dollar, Euro on Easter Holiday
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-04-06T06:33:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/ruble-stays-little-changed-versus-dollar-euro-on-easter-holiday.html
The ruble was little changed against
the dollar and the euro with European markets closed for a
public holiday.  The Russian currency gained less than 0.1 percent to 29.452
per dollar and 38.5249 per euro as of 10:30 a.m. in Moscow. The
ruble was little changed at 33.5348 against the central bank’s
target dollar-euro basket.  Western European markets are closed today for the Good
Friday holiday. Urals crude oil,  Russia ’s chief export, rose 0.8
percent to $119.46 per barrel at yesterday’s close.  Russia’s 114 billion rubles of domestic OFZ bonds due 2021
were little changed, leaving the yield steady at 7.89 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
